is going to
be the tremendous coastal
flooding.

09:36.209 --> 09:40.880 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If this system just hangs off
the New Jersey
or Delmarva Peninsula and spins
for two or

09:40.914 --> 09:44.784 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
three days, you will have a
broad area of
winds coming onshore.

09:44.818 --> 09:47.020 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That will likely lead to some
serious coastal
flooding.

09:47.053 --> 09:48.922 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: So, why is the
stalling
important?

09:48.955 --> 09:53.393 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I take it you're saying, we
would prefer it
to just rush through more
quickly?

09:53.426 --> 09:55.595 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SEAN SUBLETTE: Absolutely.

09:55.628 --> 10:00.333 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Most of the time, once these
systems push
northward, they begin to
accelerate back out

10:00.366 --> 10:02.202 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
to sea.

10:02.235 --> 10:05.271 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The steering winds, however,
with this particular
system look like they are going
to set up

10:05.305 --> 10:10.176 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
so that it's going to stall once
it clears
off the Virginia Capes and just
offshore,

10:10.210 --> 10:12.045 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
only 100 miles or.

10:12.078 --> 10:18.551 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, if it just sits and spins in
that counterclockwise
direction, you have a continuous
fetch of

10:18.585 --> 10:22.388 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
water onto shore from those
strong northeasterly
winds.

10:22.422 --> 10:24.390 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And that's what's going to pile
up the water
along the coast.

10:24.424 --> 10:29.529 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
WILLIAM BRANGHAM: All right,
Sean Sublette
from Climate Central, thanks
very much.

10:29.562 --> 10:38.872 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
SEAN SUBLETTE: Thank you.

10:38.905 --> 10:49.082 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Storms,
hurricanes and natural
disasters clearly test the
fortitude of any

10:49.115 --> 10:53.353 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
area, as we're seeing this
weekend with Hermine,
and just recently with the rains
and flooding

10:53.386 --> 10:55.154 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in Louisiana.

10:55.188 --> 10:59.692 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
We tend to focus on the
immediate aftermath
and relief, but the devastation
can last for

10:59.726 --> 11:01.461 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
years.

11:01.494 --> 11:05.198 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We have the story of how one
city leveled
by a tornado has spent years
rebuilding, and

11:05.231 --> 11:08.535 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
in some ways is better and
stronger for the
future.

11:08.568 --> 11:15.208 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The tornado that struck Joplin,
Missouri,
on May 22, 2011 was one of the
most destructive

11:15.241 --> 11:22.549 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ever in U.S. history; 161 people
were killed,
1,000 were injured, and more
than 7,000 homes

11:22.582 --> 11:24.384 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
were damaged.

11:24.417 --> 11:27.887 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When the "NewsHour" visited four
months later,
people were still literally
picking up the

11:27.921 --> 11:29.689 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
pieces of their lives.

11:29.722 --> 11:31.391 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JANE CAGE, Former Chair,
Citizens Advisory
Council: It is certainly clean,
compared with

11:31.424 --> 11:33.126 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
what it used to be.

11:33.159 --> 11:35.595 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Jane Cage, a
businesswoman
who chaired the Citizens
Advisory Council

11:35.628 --> 11:40.833 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to rebuild Joplin, told us back
then she was
worried people wouldn't come
back to the destroyed

11:40.867 --> 11:42.502 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
areas.

11:42.535 --> 11:46.573 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE CAGE: In the beginning, I
think everyone
said, I want to rebuild my
house.

11:46.606 --> 11:51.277 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And now I think people are faced
with the
reality that what they wanted,
their neighborhood

11:51.311 --> 11:54.147 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and their friends may not be in
that same
spot.

11:54.180 --> 11:57.984 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Five years
later, Cage took
us on a tour of the same
neighborhood.

11:58.017 --> 12:02.221 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE CAGE: I think this is, in
some ways,
one of the best recovered
neighborhoods.

12:02.255 --> 12:04.424 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
They're nicer houses and larger
houses overall.

12:04.457 --> 12:08.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: She says one
of the main
things that Joplin got right in
the aftermath

12:08.328 --> 12:10.263 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
was encouraging residents to
stay.

12:10.296 --> 12:16.202 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JANE CAGE: We concentrated on
keeping our
population in Joplin, because we
saw what

12:16.235 --> 12:20.673 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
happened in other cities that
experienced
disasters.

12:20.707 --> 12:25.345 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I think one of the first
things that we
did to make that happen was, our
school superintendent

12:25.378 --> 12:28.014 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
made the promise that we would
start school
on time.

12:28.047 --> 12:32.952 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Five schools
were completely
wiped out in the storm,
including Joplin High

12:32.986 --> 12:34.554 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
School.

12:34.587 --> 12:39.792 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
When we visited in 2011, classes
had just
begun in an abandoned shopping
mall.

12:39.826 --> 12:44.497 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Now a brand-new state-of-the-art
high school
has opened on the original site.

12:44.530 --> 12:49.068 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's just across the street from
where sophomore
Blake Dean's house was
flattened.

12:49.102 --> 12:51.738 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Dean described how he rode out
the storm in
a backyard shelter.

12:51.771 --> 12:55.141 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
BLAKE DEAN, Student: Sure
enough, we start
hearing a kind of freight train
noise.

12:55.174 --> 12:59.512 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it just starts getting
really loud and
the pressure starts building.

12:59.545 --> 13:03.983 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And then we all kind of just
huddled up in
the shelter, and it just blew
over it.

13:04.017 --> 13:08.788 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: His family
chose to rebuild
on the same lot a bigger and
better house.

13:08.821 --> 13:11.090 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And he says the school is also
bigger and
better.

13:11.124 --> 13:12.992 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
BLAKE DEAN: Oh, it's just
awesome.

13:13.026 --> 13:16.396 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It's so -- I mean, it's so much
bigger than
the last one and there's so much
more opportunity.

13:16.429 --> 13:21.067 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: In fact,
bigger and better
is how many in Joplin now
describe the city

13:21.100 --> 13:22.602 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
as a whole.

13:22.635 --> 13:26.572 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The population has actually
grown by 1,000
people over the last five years.

13:26.606 --> 13:30.877 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And fellow high school football
player Maurice
Aubrey says the sense of
community has become

13:30.910 --> 13:32.779 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
stronger too.

13:32.812 --> 13:35.915 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MAURICE AUBREY, Student: Now we
have this
single past experience that
links us all together,

13:35.948 --> 13:37.183 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
as before.

13:37.216 --> 13:40.353 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, it just makes it -- it's
made it so much
better, I think.

13:40.386 --> 13:44.223 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARCINDA HEMPEN, Joplin,
Missouri: My complex
was this portion right here, and
my apartment

13:44.257 --> 13:45.992 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
was right here.

13:46.025 --> 13:48.828 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Marcinda
Hempen is one of
those people who took advantage
of those new

13:48.861 --> 13:50.663 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
opportunities.

13:50.697 --> 13:53.499 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She was living in an apartment
and huddled
in the bathtub when the storm
passed through.

13:53.533 --> 13:58.404 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARCINDA HEMPEN: The weirdest
thing was, after
it was all done, it was so quiet
that I thought,

13:58.438 --> 14:00.807 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
am I dead?

14:00.840 --> 14:01.874 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Did I not make it?

14:01.908 --> 14:03.710 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Is this what it's like to be
dead?

14:03.743 --> 14:07.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Hempen, a
single mom of
two now-grown boys, said, prior
to the storm,

14:07.780 --> 14:12.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
she couldn't afford to buy a
house, but thanks
to a $20 million federal loan
program which

14:12.418 --> 14:16.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
helped her with a down-payment,
she owns a
home in one of the hardest-hit
areas.

14:16.489 --> 14:18.758 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
MARCINDA HEMPEN: It's still a
little unreal.

14:18.791 --> 14:20.059 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
I own this.

14:20.093 --> 14:21.060 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
This is all mine.

14:21.094 --> 14:22.428 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
I can paint a wall.

14:22.462 --> 14:24.997 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I can do whatever I want to do,
and nobody
can tell me different.

14:25.031 --> 14:29.535 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
HARI SREENIVASAN: The
community-wide effort,
along with help from all levels
of government

14:29.569 --> 14:34.240 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and hundreds of volunteer
organizations from
around the country, has changed
the face of

14:34.273 --> 14:35.708 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the city.

14:35.742 --> 14:39.679 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Nearly 2,000 new homes have been
built; 300
new businesses have opened.

14:39.712 --> 14:44.417 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And thanks to $30 million from
the federal
government, the city has a new
sewer system,

14:44.450 --> 14:50.089 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
new electrical grid, and new
storm shelters
in every school and public
building.

14:50.123 --> 14:55.561 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
There are also new parks,
complete with basketball
courts, playgrounds and water
features.

14:55.595 --> 15:01.400 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
St. John's Mercy Hospital, which
was completely
destroyed, has been rebuilt on a
new site,

15:01.434 --> 15:07.106 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and has $11 million worth of
upgrades to protect
from future tornadoes, including
windows that

15:07.140 --> 15:14.881 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
can sustain winds up to 250
miles an hour,
fortified safe zones on every
floor, and a

15:14.914 --> 15:19.952 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
450-foot reinforced tunnel,
which houses generators,
water and data communications.

15:19.986 --> 15:24.157 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But for all of the signs of new
growth in
Joplin, there is one area where
the healing

15:24.190 --> 15:26.058 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
has been more difficult.

15:26.092 --> 15:31.030 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Cases of mental distress and
trauma have more
than doubled over the past five
years, affecting

15:31.063 --> 15:35.168 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
people like Marian Kelly, who
showed us the
crawl space where she rode out
thee storm.

15:35.201 --> 15:38.638 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARIAN KELLY, Joplin, Missouri:
But, at some
point I felt the air getting
sucked out of

15:38.671 --> 15:40.273 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the crawl space around me.

15:40.306 --> 15:42.942 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And I thought, this is how I'm
going to die.

15:42.975 --> 15:45.144 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: She was
relatively lucky.

15:45.178 --> 15:50.483 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Her house was damaged, but not
destroyed,
and she emerged with just some
cuts and bruises.

15:50.516 --> 15:52.752 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But the emotional scars have
been much deeper.

15:52.785 --> 15:59.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MARIAN KELLY: For me, the
post-traumatic stress
disorder has manifested itself
mostly in a

15:59.292 --> 16:03.229 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
heightened emotional response to
things.

16:03.262 --> 16:10.069 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I get anxious or upset in ways
that I wouldn't
have before.

16:10.102 --> 16:13.105 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Also, the concentration issues
are there.

16:13.139 --> 16:15.107 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
That's why there's alarms for
everything on
my phone.

16:15.141 --> 16:18.010 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
That's why everything has to be
written down.

16:18.044 --> 16:22.114 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: She has been
able to hold
down a job, but she says that's
thanks to

16:22.148 --> 16:25.184 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
medication and regular
counseling sessions.

16:25.218 --> 16:27.220 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
She's not sure she will ever
fully recover.

16:27.253 --> 16:31.457 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
MARIAN KELLY: It's been
difficult for me to
accept that I might not get all
of this back,

16:31.490 --> 16:32.625 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the things that I have lost.

16:32.658 --> 16:34.894 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
I have shaved off a few I.Q.
points, you know?

16:34.927 --> 16:37.797 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I don't know if I can expect
there -- to
get them back.

16:37.830 --> 16:41.701 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: While Kelly
still struggles
with her memories of that
terrible day, she

16:41.734 --> 16:45.037 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
is proud of the city for showing
such resilience
in the aftermath.

16:45.071 --> 16:50.776 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She is also hopeful that the
many young people
who have moved to Joplin since
the storm will

16:50.810 --> 16:54.013 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
bring new energy and life to the
community.

16:54.046 --> 16:58.117 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That new life is evident in the
downtown,
which had been largely abandoned
before the

16:58.150 --> 16:59.318 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
tornado hit.

16:59.352 --> 17:03.856 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Now it's dotted with hip
restaurants, bars
and lofts.

17:03.890 --> 17:07.226 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Rachel Grindle, who just moved
to Joplin from
Long Beach, California, is
impressed.

17:07.260 --> 17:10.196 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
RACHEL GRINDLE, Joplin,
Missouri: Our first
week living in Joplin, we were
invited to

17:10.229 --> 17:18.070 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Friday night wine share, which
is this networking
group for people our age who are
career-minded

17:18.104 --> 17:20.573 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
and city-focused.

17:20.606 --> 17:23.843 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And after that, everybody came
here to Infuxn
afterwards.

17:23.876 --> 17:25.544 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And we went out to dinner after
that.

17:25.578 --> 17:33.986 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I looked at my husband, and
I was like,
I feel like we're living more of
the L.A.

17:34.020 --> 17:35.821 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
lifestyle in Joplin than we ever
did in Long
Beach.

17:35.855 --> 17:39.025 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Reminders of
the storm can
still be found everywhere in
Joplin, whether

17:39.058 --> 17:43.696 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it's the memorials to the people
who lost
their lives, or to the miles and
miles of

17:43.729 --> 17:45.598 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
treeless neighborhoods.

17:45.631 --> 17:49.635 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But five years later, the signs
of progress
that have emerged from that
tragic day have

17:49.669 --> 17:54.807 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
become a model for other
communities who have
suffered catastrophic disasters.

17:54.840 --> 18:00.713 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
For the "PBS NewsHour," I'm Hari
Sreenivasan.

18:00.746 --> 18:09.889 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
HARI SREENIVASAN: Stay with us.

18:09.922 --> 18:14.493 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Coming up on the "NewsHour": the
controversy
over an NFL quarterback refusing
to stand

18:14.527 --> 18:19.265 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
for the national anthem; and
Mark Shields
and David Brooks take on the
week's news.

18:19.298 --> 18:24.303 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But, first: Today, the FBI
released two key
documents about its
investigation into the

18:24.337 --> 18:28.808 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
private e-mail server Hillary
Clinton used
when she was secretary of state.

18:28.841 --> 18:34.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
One contains the agency's notes
from Clinton's
FBI interview, and the other is
a 47-page

18:34.780 --> 18:37.550 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
summary of the FBI's findings.

18:37.583 --> 18:40.119 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
NPR's Carrie Johnson is covering
the story
and joins me now.

18:40.152 --> 18:42.855 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
So, what's new about the
documents that were
released today?

18:42.888 --> 18:48.294 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
CARRIE JOHNSON, NPR: There are
several new
details, including really a
sense of what

18:48.327 --> 18:53.165 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
Hillary Clinton told FBI
investigators in
that three-and-a-half-hour
interview at FBI

18:53.199 --> 18:54.667 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
headquarters on July 2.

18:54.700 --> 18:59.405 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hari, she said she used this
personal server
as a matter of convenience.

18:59.438 --> 19:06.078 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
She never had a concern that she
or anybody
close to her was mishandling
classified information,

19:06.112 --> 19:11.884 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
and that she actually doesn't
recall attending
